snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Brad! So, science has proven that coconut oil and olive oil penetrate the hair shaft. Coconut oil has the highest absorption rate due to the molecular structure. This is why over use of coconut oil can actually cause hair to become brittle and break. Olive oil is the second smallest on a molecular level and is ideal for adding moisture to the hair.

However, since these are actually absorbed, I would think using this prior to a color would affect your results, given it would cause an issue with the color deposit into the hair shaft. I tend to use olive oil on my ends if they are dry, but I don't leave it on long, and it comes out very soft (after a wash and deep condition).

Hope that helps! :)

However, since these are actually absorbed, I would think using this prior to a color would affect your results, given it would cause an issue with the color deposit into the hair shaft. snippet.textDisplay: Love the videos as always, thanks for making an all natural hair vid! XX. Also, a lot of black girls have very different textured hair e.g. I have very thin light curly hair at the back of my head, kinky in the middle and very loosely curled hair at the front. My hairdresser used to relax my hair beginning in he middle because that took the longest time to "breakdown". It's different for everyone, so it all depends on what you got working with.
snippet.textOriginal: Love the videos as always, thanks for making an all natural hair vid! XX.
